From: Antigravity <antigravity@google.com>
Date: Sat, 2 May 2026 14:15:00 -0700
Subject: [PATCH 4/4] docs/tracing: add io_uring wakeup attribution example

This documentation patch provides an example of how to use the
newly introduced io_uring_cq_wakeup tracepoint to measure
the delay between completion posting and userspace execution.

Example bpftrace logic:
tracepoint:io_uring:io_uring_complete { @done[args->ctx] = nsecs; }
tracepoint:io_uring:io_uring_cq_wakeup { 
    if (@done[args->ctx]) {
        printf("Wakeup delay: %llu ns\n", nsecs - @done[args->ctx]);
    }
}

Signed-off-by: Antigravity <antigravity@google.com>
---
 Documentation/trace/io_uring.rst | 15 +++++++++++++++
 1 file changed, 15 insertions(+)

diff --git a/Documentation/trace/io_uring.rst b/Documentation/trace/io_uring.rst
index ...
--- a/Documentation/trace/io_uring.rst
+++ b/Documentation/trace/io_uring.rst
@@ -100,3 +100,18 @@ complete - posted when a request finishes.
 issue    - posted when a request is dispatched to a driver.
 submit   - posted when an SQE is accepted from userspace.
 
+Wait and Wakeup Attribution
+---------------------------
+
+The `io_uring_cq_wakeup` tracepoint allows measuring the scheduling
+latency of the completion path.
+
+.. code-block:: none
+
+    # bpftrace -e '
+    tracepoint:io_uring:io_uring_complete { @c[args->ctx] = nsecs; }
+    tracepoint:io_uring:io_uring_cq_wakeup {
+        if (@c[args->ctx]) {
+            printf("ctx %p wakeup delay: %d us\n", args->ctx, (nsecs - @c[args->ctx])/1000);
+        }
+    }'
